{
  "stem": "3022.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 156,
      "text": "But once we came to Flossenburg, to Germany, we were stripped of everything that we owned.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 157,
      "text": "All we were given is the striped uniform, the wooden clogs, and a metal plate on our [INAUDIBLE], into which to receive our food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 158,
      "text": "And the spoon, the handle of it, we would thin out with a rock or something, to serve as a knife.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 159,
      "text": "Because you were not allowed to have a knife.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 160,
      "text": "All other private possessions were forbidden.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 161,
      "text": "I managed to hide two things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 162,
      "text": "One was a picture of my mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 163,
      "text": "And the other one was a toothbrush.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 164,
      "text": "The picture of my mother, I kept in order to be able to dream about my home, the love, and the warmth of pre-war life.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 165,
      "text": "And the toothbrush was my only connection to civilized life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 166,
      "text": "The very mundane function of brushing your teeth-- even without any toothpaste, with bleeding gums, and I lacked quite a few teeth at that time from the beatings-- it was what kept me close to civilization.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 167,
      "text": "It was my contact with normality.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 168,
      "text": "So these things, I was able to hide on my body.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 169,
      "text": "And when we got to Dachau, we had to go to the [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 170,
      "text": "We knew that we're going to be searched.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 171,
      "text": "And I took-- I hid in a rag the picture of my mother and my toothbrush, and I hid it under a barrack, when we went to [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 172,
      "text": "And I made sure that nobody saw it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 173,
      "text": "Apparently, somebody must have seen them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 174,
      "text": "When I came out, it was gone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 175,
      "text": "For me, this was the end.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 176,
      "text": "At that time, I made the decision to kill myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 177,
      "text": "Because there was nothing for me to live for-- not memories.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 178,
      "text": "And I lost contact from being a human being.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
